&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://healthesystems.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/HR-4919-Greenhouse-Graphic-v5.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Healthesystems offers workplace flexibility with our Work-From-Home model, and a competitive compensation and benefits package including healthcare coverage, PTO, paid holidays, 401(k), company-provided life insurance/disability coverage, wellness options, and more.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&amp;nbsp; we are unable to hire in every state&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sales Enablement &amp;amp; Proposals Manager is a senior individual contributor responsible for enabling sales effectiveness in complex B2B sales environments through high‑impact enablement campaigns and assets, disciplined RFP execution, and strong ownership of proposal workflows and tooling. This role supports a focused, relationship‑driven sales model and ensures sales teams are equipped with the right campaigns, content, and processes to move longer‑cycle, highly considered opportunities forward. The role partners closely with Sales, Marketing, and subject matter experts across the organization to translate strategy into clear, sales‑ready execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities: “To simplify complexities for each customer.”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute and operationalize sales enablement programs and campaigns within CRM and marketing automation platforms (e.g., HubSpot, Pardot/Salesforce), identifying opportunities to incorporate AI‑enabled tools and emerging technologies to enhance content delivery, personalization, and workflow efficiency, ensuring enablement assets are activated, accessible, and aligned to defined sales motions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Sales to deliver buyer‑aligned enablement support, translating established positioning, value propositions, and sales strategies into effective sales narratives, plays, and assets for the field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure enablement and proposal materials remain current and on‑strategy, aligning to approved positioning, GTM priorities, and messaging while applying appropriate levels of customization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support priority and late‑stage opportunities with tailored proposal and enablement materials, executing against deal strategy and buyer needs defined in partnership with Sales and leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage the end‑to‑end RFP/RFI process and tooling, including intake, timelines, coordination with subject matter experts, quality control, and final submission.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and continuously improve the RFP and proposal content library, including standard narratives, win themes, reusable responses, and best practices to drive consistency, speed, and differentiation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer and optimize proposal and enablement tools, workflows, and templates, ensuring ease of use, collaboration, and efficiency across Sales, Marketing, and Operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write, edit, and refine proposals, executive summaries, and enablement content, ensuring clarity, consistency, and compelling narrative flow while avoiding generic or overly templated language.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a feedback conduit between Sales and Marketing, capturing insights on objections, content gaps, and asset usability, and sharing recommendations to inform ongoing enablement and automation improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications/Education/Certifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Communications, Business, or a related field, or equivalent combination of education and experience.&lt;/li&gt

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://healthesystems.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/HR-4919-Greenhouse-Graphic-v5.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Healthesystems offers workplace flexibility with our Work-From-Home model, and a competitive compensation and benefits package including healthcare coverage, PTO, paid holidays, 401(k), company-provided life insurance/disability coverage, wellness options, and more.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&amp;nbsp; we are unable to hire in every state&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt; This position is responsible for providing technical leadership, expertise and guidance related to the design, development, and implementation of Appian-based Low-Code Application Platform (LCAP) software solutions that enable our business objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Solutions Architect, Senior will apply proven communication skills, problem-solving skills, and knowledge of best practices, acting as a technical advisor, to provide leadership and guidance in the planning and coordination of design, development and implementation of our mission-critical systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities: “To simplify complexities for each customer.”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide architecture leadership and Appian expertise while collaboratively working with stakeholders in all areas of the business and IT, aligning Appian solutions to support company objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continually facilitate and assist with efforts to define Appian-centric enterprise solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acts as the design authority for Appian-based solutions, guiding solution architecture and design decisions across business-critical applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure effective governance of defined industry, company, and Appian-specific standards and patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate and build prototypes, create reference architectures, and design effective solutions that leverage the Appian platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continually stay abreast on LCAP trends and lead the research and development efforts accordingly through proof-of-concept implementations, workshops, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide guidance, coaching, architectural assessments, and Appian mentorship for various IT teams and initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create prototypes and design innovative and effective Appian-based solutions that align with organization’s objectives and maintain competitive market advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with peers and various IT groups in continuously creating, assessing and updating LCAP standards, guidelines and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion product design, solution design and industry best practices in building and delivering best in class software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively communicate using written, oral, non-verbal, and active listening skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications/Education/Certifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree preferably in a computer science/engineering related field plus 8-10 years of related experience; and/or equivalent combination of education and experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experienced in leading and implementing the design and delivery of complex Appian-based solutions, including case management, integrations, and data-centric applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in Healthcare and Knowledge of Workers’ Compensation industry is a plus.&lt;/p&gt;
